`[ExpectedException]` was removed in MSTest v4. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` inside the test body.

**Before (v3):**
```csharp
[ExpectedException(typeof(InvalidOperationException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    service.DoSomething();
}
```

**After (v4):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => service.DoSomething());
}
```

Key points:
- **Async methods** â†’ use `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>(() => ...)`
- **`AllowDerivedTypes = true`** â†’ use `Assert.Throws<T>` (matches derived types) instead of `ThrowsExactly` (exact match)
- Wrap only the **throwing call** in the lambda â€” keep setup code outside

The analyzer **MSTEST0006** flags this in v3, so you can fix it before upgrading. Want me to apply this fix to your `ValidationServiceTests.cs`?
